# EduPulse — 1-Page Problem Brief
### For EDVentures 2026 | SDG 4: Quality Education

---

## 🎤 The Hook (Founder Story — say this out loud)

> *"I sat in a lecture. The teacher moved on. I was lost. I didn't raise my hand — I was scared of looking stupid in front of 60 people. By the end of the semester, I had failed the module. That moment is why I built EduPulse."*

---

## ❌ The Problem

**In every classroom, right now, students are silently failing.**

Not because they aren't trying. Because they're too afraid to say *"I don't understand."*

| Statistic | Source |
|---|---|
| **72%** of students don't ask questions in class due to fear of judgment | Core.ac.uk / NIH Research |
| **50%** of students in large classes never ask a single question all semester | NIH Study |
| **1 in 4** university students drop out — globally, that's hundreds of millions | Educations.com, 2024 |
| Universities lose **$21,000 USD (≈ HKD 163,800)** per dropout student | AttendanceRadar Research |

### Who suffers?
- 🎓 **Students** — fall behind silently, lose confidence, and eventually drop out
- 👨‍🏫 **Teachers** — teach into the void with no real-time feedback
- 🏫 **Institutions** — lose tuition revenue and reputation

### Why is this happening NOW?
- Post-COVID: classrooms are larger, attention spans shorter, and the silence is louder
- Traditional feedback tools (clickers, surveys) are slow, public, and ignored
- **No tool today closes the loop between confusion → detection → remedy in real-time**

---

## ✅ The Solution — EduPulse

> *One tap. Anonymous. Instant.*

A student taps "I'm lost" on their phone. In 3 seconds, the teacher sees a live confusion signal on their dashboard — mapped to the exact topic being taught. After class, AI drafts a targeted review email and diagnostic quiz automatically.

**No app. No account. No embarrassment.**

---

## 📊 Measurable Impact (Outcome Statement)

> *"EduPulse targets a 20% reduction in repeat confusion signals within 4 sessions, and a measurable decrease in first-semester dropout risk among pilot cohorts."*

| Metric | Target |
|---|---|
| Reduction in repeat confusion per topic | 20% within 4 sessions |
| Teacher response time to confusion | From days → minutes |
| At-risk students flagged early | 3–4 weeks before dropout |
| Market opportunity (Asia Pacific EdTech) | **$11 Billion USD / HKD 85.8 Billion** (2024, CAGR 23.4%) |

---

## 🌍 SDG 4 Alignment

EduPulse directly addresses **SDG 4.1** (quality education for all) and **SDG 4.c** (improving teacher quality) by:
- Giving every student — regardless of confidence — an equal voice in the classroom
- Turning confusion data into teacher action within minutes, not weeks
- Building an institutional early-warning system for dropout risk

---

*EduPulse — Teaching doesn't stop when class ends.*
